  "description": [
    "STRICT ALIEN LAW URGED BY HUSBAND Advocates More Deporta tions of Lawbreakers in Radio Forum Address Continued From Tenth Page the board of review in his behalf In the month of July 419 such cases were considered on appeal to the Secretary Before the quota limit law of 1924 went into effect thousands of well ta tentioned immigrants crossed the ocean and applied at United States ports only to And that they could not qualify for admission under the immigration law and were necessarily returned by the steamship companies to the country of origin Since the inauguration of the S resent system of Inspection abroad owever the relectlon of those aho apply and are in possession of proper consular visas has been reduced to a minimum In fact only five or six out of every 10000 immigrants who have qualified under the consular and tech nical adviser plan are now turned back at united States ports which of course means that the system is as nearly 100 per cent perfect as anything that hu man ingenuity and effort can devise I want to digress a little at this point to refer to the splendid cooper ation that exists among the"
